<p>For friendly URL purposes I'm using the following IIS rules:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;system.webServer&gt;     &lt;rewrite&gt;         &lt;rules&gt;             &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_1" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                 &lt;match url="^lesson$" /&gt;                 &lt;conditions&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                 &lt;/conditions&gt;                 &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="lesson.php" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;             &lt;/rule&gt;             &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_2" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                 &lt;match url="^lesson/$" /&gt;                 &lt;conditions&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                 &lt;/conditions&gt;                 &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="lesson.php" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;             &lt;/rule&gt;             &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_3" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                 &lt;match url="^lesson/(.+)\.(.+)$" /&gt;                 &lt;conditions&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                 &lt;/conditions&gt;                 &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="{R:1}.{R:2}" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;             &lt;/rule&gt;             &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_4" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                 &lt;match url="^lesson/(.+)$" /&gt;                 &lt;conditions&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                 &lt;/conditions&gt;                 &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="lesson.php?chapter={R:1}" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;             &lt;/rule&gt;         &lt;/rules&gt;     &lt;/rewrite&gt; &lt;/system.webServer&gt; </code></pre>  <p>it has the following effects:</p>  <pre><code>www.domain.com/lesson -&gt; www.domain.com/lesson.php www.domain.com/lesson/ -&gt; www.domain.com/lesson.php www.domain.com/lesson/chapter1 -&gt; www.domain.com/lesson.php?chapter=chapter1 </code></pre>  <p>All is nice and good except for when the name of the capter includes a period.</p>  <p>for example</p>  <pre><code>www.domain.com/lesson/chapter2: numbers larger than 1.000.000 </code></pre>  <p>In that case I get a 404 page not found. Is there a way to solve this ?</p>  <p>I found this post: <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5070501/iis7-url-rewriting-with-period">IIS7: URL Rewriting with period</a></p>  <p>and I altered the web.config to be:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;configuration&gt;     &lt;system.web&gt;         &lt;httpRuntime relaxedUrlToFileSystemMapping="true"/&gt;     &lt;/system.web&gt;     &lt;system.webServer&gt;         &lt;modules runAllManagedModulesForAllRequests="true"&gt;&lt;/modules&gt;         &lt;rewrite&gt;             &lt;rules&gt;                 &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_1" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                     &lt;match url="^lesson$" /&gt;                     &lt;conditions&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;/conditions&gt;                     &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="lesson.php" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;                 &lt;/rule&gt;                 &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_2" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                     &lt;match url="^lesson/$" /&gt;                     &lt;conditions&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;/conditions&gt;                     &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="lesson.php" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;                 &lt;/rule&gt;                 &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_3"&gt;                     &lt;match url="^lesson/(.+)\.(.+)$" /&gt;                     &lt;conditions&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;/conditions&gt;                     &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="{R:1}.{R:2}" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;                 &lt;/rule&gt;                 &lt;rule name="Fr_lesson_4" stopProcessing="true"&gt;                     &lt;match url="^lesson/(.+)$" /&gt;                     &lt;conditions&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsFile" negate="true" /&gt;                         &lt;add input="{REQUEST_FILENAME}" matchType="IsDirectory" negate="true" /&gt;                     &lt;/conditions&gt;                     &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="lesson.php?chapter={R:1}" appendQueryString="false" /&gt;                 &lt;/rule&gt;             &lt;/rules&gt;         &lt;/rewrite&gt;     &lt;/system.webServer&gt; &lt;/configuration&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But it doesn't solve the problem. Any ideas?</p>  <p>Thank you in advance</p>